# Public API Documentation

## Doc Comments

- **Public items** (`pub fn`, `pub struct`, `pub enum`, `pub const` re-exported from lib): add a `///` doc comment describing purpose and, for functions, args/return/errors where non-obvious.
- **Modules**: add `//!` module-level docs for non-trivial modules (e.g. inference, model, kernels).

```rust
// ✅ GOOD
/// Runs a forward pass; returns logits for the last token.
pub fn forward(&self, input_ids: &[usize]) -> Result<Vec<f32>> { ... }

// ❌ BAD (no doc)
pub fn forward(&self, input_ids: &[usize]) -> Result<Vec<f32>> { ... }
```

- Keep doc text in English (see project English-only rule).
